'''Barnim IV of Pomerania''' (1325 &ndash; 22 August 1365) was a [[Duke]] of Pomerania-Wolgast-R<U+00FC>gen.

He was the second son of Duke [[Wartislaw IV, Duke of Pomerania|Wartislaw]] of Pomerania-Wolgast and the brother of [[Bogislaw V, Duke of Pomerania|Bogislaw V]] and [[Wartislaw V, Duke of Pomerania|Wartislaw V]].

He married Sophie of [[Werle]], the daughter of [[John II of Werle]].  They had two sons, [[Wartislaw VI, Duke of Pomerania|Wartislaw VI]] and [[Bogislaw VI, Duke of Pomerania|Bogislaw VI]], and a daughter, Elisabeth, who married Duke [[Magnus I, Duke of Mecklenburg|Magnus I]] of Mecklenburg.

He inherited Pomerania-Wolgast-R<U+00FC>gen when his father died in 1326.  He was one year old at the time.  He shared a guardian with his brother Bogislaw V, Duke of Pommern-Wolgast-R<U+00FC>gen.

Emperor [[Charles IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Charles IV]] granted Barnim IV [[Imperial immediacy]] in 1348.

